Zarate, who plays best in an attacking left-sided role, is among a host of targets for West Ham this summer with manager Allardyce having a budget of £20million to spend.

Free agents Joleon Lescott and Martin Olsson are wanted by the 59-year-old boss, as he looks to beef up his defence for next season. 

